    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>
                        <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/37">Rodulfus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs>, dietro la supplica di <persName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#people/45">Lantpertus Mediolanensis</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">archiepiscopus</rs> et <persName key="#Bishops"
                            ref="#people/78">Adalbertus</persName> sanctae sedis Bergamensis <rs
                            key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs> et <persName key="#Marquis/duke"
                            ref="#people/23">Bonefacius</persName>
                        <rs key="#Marquis/duke">marchio</rs>, concede e conferma al monastero
                        fondato dall’<rs key="#Queen">imperatrice</rs>
                        <persName key="#Queen" ref="#people/55">Angelberga</persName> e dedicato da
                            <persName key="#Abbesses" ref="#people/67">Berta</persName> a <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/53">S. Sisto</orgName>
                        <geogName ref="#estates/40"
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >quasdam <rs
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >curtes</rs>
                            <placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/33">Vuardestallam</placeName>
                        </geogName> scilicet, <geogName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/38">
                            <placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/32">Luzariam</placeName>
                        </geogName>, <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/77"><placeName ref="#places/361"
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Litora Paludiana</placeName></geogName>, <geogName
                            ref="#estates/80"
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><placeName ref="#places/362"
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Villolę</placeName></geogName>, <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/42">
                            <placeName key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property" ref="#places/34"
                                >Piguniarius</placeName>
                        </geogName>, e tutte le cose che la predetta imperatrice trasferì al
                        cenobio. Il monastero è affidato a Berta che ne sarà dominatrix, ordinatrix
                        atque retrix. Concediamo tutti i <rs key="#Landed_possessions">possessi
                            mobiles ac immobiles</rs>, tam per <rs key="#Parchment_documents"
                            >cartulas</rs> quamque extra cartulas o pervenuti a qualsiasi altro
                        titolo, acquisiti o da acquisire, tutto quello che è stato concesso dagli
                        imperatori, atque <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellulam</rs> quandam que
                        antiquitus <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/1508"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                            >Monasterium</orgName> dicebatur non procul a <placeName
                            ref="#places/43">Placentina urbe</placeName> sitam, loco qui <placeName
                            ref="#places/14"
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Caput Trebiae</placeName> vocatur, che era stata data da <persName
                            ref="#people/80" key="#Emperor/king">Carlomanno</persName> al monastero
                            <rs key="#Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure">proprietario iure</rs>. <rs
                            key="#Personal_statuses">Familias quoque utriusque sexus et
                            conditionis</rs> cum <rs key="#Curtes">curtibus</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Churches/religious_bodies">cappellis</rs> e segue l’elenco di
                        tutte le appendici. Per chiunque violerà gli accordi, <rs key="#Penalty"
                            >pena di £150 d’oro</rs>, metà da pagare <rs key="#Camera_regis">camerę
                            nostre</rs>, metà a Berta. SM Rodulfi piissimi regis.<persName
                            key="#Chancellor"><name ref="Mannus">Manno</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> ad vicem venerabilis <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops" ref="#people/1500">Beati</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopi</rs> et <rs key="#Archchancellor"
                            >archicancellarii</rs> rec. et sub. Data. Actum <placeName
                            ref="#places/59">Veronę</placeName>, in Christi nomine feliciter,
                        amen.</ab>
